cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper proposes a game theoretic approach for achieving efficient computation offloading for mobile cloud computing, which involves distributed decision making among mobile device users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also analyzes the structural property of the game, which suggests a possible fit with cs.GT (Game Theory). The use of mobile devices and cloud computing may also suggest a fit with cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the proposed mechanism for achieving efficient computation offloading may involve optimization techniques, which could suggest a fit with cs.MA (Machine Learning).
